overflow.com/questions/38418402/align-icons-and-text-in-qlistview-centered\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/38418402/align-icons-and-text-in-qlistview-centered</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>I will need to review my code, because I have managed to make a decent layout, but not sure if it addresses problems from the above links.</p>\n<h2 id=\"custom-widget\" style=\"position:relative;\">Custom widget<a href=\"#custom-widget\" aria-label=\"custom widget permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>And if nothing works from stylesheets, then just create a new widget. It's not that hard as you may think.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://zetcode.com/gui/qt5/customwidget/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://zetcode.com/gui/qt5/customwidget/</a></p>","excerpt":"You have few approaches for styling your Qt app. QSS Stylesheet Reference https://doc.qt.io/archives/qt-4.8/stylesheet-reference.html#border…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#qss-stylesheet\">QSS Stylesheet</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#reference\">Reference</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#examples\">Examples</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#custom-widget\">Custom widget</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>","fields":{"socialcard":"gatsby-plugin-social-card/41966be9-96e3-5a87-8c0c-e7bf77dd8214.jpg"},"frontmatter":{"date":"July 23, 2021","published"